## Slide 7 – Responsibility #1 · Data Translator 💬

**Layout suggestion:** Title left · key activities right.

**Key points:**
- Act as the **strategic bridge** between Consumer & Commercial business needs and delivery teams across IT, DI&A, and external partners/vendors
- Translate Consumer goals into **clear, implementable requirements** – ensuring shared understanding and fast decisions
- **Key tasks:**
  - Identify the right data source for each need (system, vendor feed, dataset/view)
  - Facilitate **discovery & requirement workshops**; turn business questions into epics/stories with acceptance criteria
  - Coordinate day-to-day alignment with internal teams and vendors when clarifications are needed (e.g. API method, scope details, integration approach)

**Speaker notes:**
This is our most visible responsibility. Picture this: a brand manager says "I want to know which consumers respond to a flavor launch." Our job is to translate that into: which systems hold the data, what user stories we need, what acceptance criteria look like, who builds it, and how it ladders up to a business KPI. Every requirement workshop is a chance to either save the project weeks or burn weeks of rework later.

**Visual suggestions:**
- Workshop icon · arrows flowing from "Business question" → "Epic with acceptance criteria"
- Example side-by-side: bad requirement vs good requirement

