## Slide 8 – Responsibility #2 · Data Governance & Architecture 🛡️

**Layout suggestion:** Two-column (Governance left · Architecture right).

**Key points:**
- Operationalize a governance model that ensures Consumer & Commercial data initiatives meet PMI's standards for **documentation, architecture, and traceability**
- Collaborate with **DI&A architects** and **IT platform owners** to ensure solutions are modern, scalable, and aligned with enterprise architecture
- **Key tasks:**
  - Maintain an up-to-date **inventory of interfaces & applications** (apps + integrations + dependencies)
  - Standardize "**definition of done**" – documentation + training + support handoff
  - Ensure **traceability and governance** for integrations (formal lists of APIs/interfaces, ownership, change control)
  - **Validate delivered solutions** with end users → feedback → backlog refinement

**Speaker notes:**
Without this, IT CX becomes a series of one-off deliveries that nobody can maintain. Architecture and governance is what makes our work survive past go-live. It's also what gives us credibility with InfoSec, Architecture Review Boards, and DI&A. Treat traceability as oxygen – without it, the value evaporates.

**Visual suggestions:**
- Shield icon for governance · gears icon for architecture
- Mini diagram of an interface inventory

