## Slide 9 – Responsibility #3 · Consumer Insights & BI 📊

**Layout suggestion:** Pipeline diagram (data → dashboard → adoption).

**Key points:**
- Drive adoption and oversee the **delivery & lifecycle of data products and BI solutions** supporting Consumer & Commercial initiatives (analytics, engagement platforms, CRM insights, performance dashboards)
- Ensure **value realization, adoption, and business impact**
- Strengthen collaboration with DI&A teams to clarify goals, benefits, and the data sources driving decisions
- **Key tasks:**
  - Drive end-to-end delivery/enhancements of Consumer insights and BI (roadmap, prioritization, release readiness, adoption follow-up)
  - Co-define **KPIs and success metrics** with DI&A and business owners
  - Track **adoption and business impact**; run enablement sessions and "how to use" playbooks
  - Maintain an **inventory of Consumer reports & dashboards** (owner, purpose, refresh cadence, sources, audience) to reduce duplication

**Speaker notes:**
Building a dashboard is the easy part. Driving adoption is the hard part. Our job is not "delivery" – it's "value realization." A dashboard nobody uses is a cost; a dashboard that changes how the business decides is value. Always close the loop with the business owner: did we move a KPI? If not, why?

