## Slide 18 – End-to-end Demand Management process ⚙️

**Layout suggestion:** Horizontal 9-step process flow.

**Key points (9 steps):**
1. **Submit demand** (intake form / Jira ticket)
2. **Define requirements** (workshops · BRD · stories with acceptance criteria)
3. **Prioritization** (value · risk · compliance · effort · dependencies)
4. **Estimation** (vendor estimate · capacity check)
5. **Sprint planning** (slot into vendor sprints)
6. **Development** (vendor + DI&A)
7. **UAT** (business validates)
8. **Deploy to PRD** (release management)
9. **Close & communicate** (adoption + benefits + retro)

**RACI summary:**
- **Business Stakeholders** – submit & validate
- **DI&A Business Partner / Engineer / PBI Developer** – design & build
- **IT Data Service Manager / Demand Manager** – orchestrate · prioritize · escalate (this is Ivan)
- **IT Vendor (BPO & Tech / Coforge)** – execute build
- **Business Owner** – sign-off & benefits realization

**Speaker notes:**
This is the workflow you'll see every week. Steps 1–3 are where IT CX adds the most value. Steps 4–6 are where vendors do the heavy lifting. Steps 7–9 are where business validates and we measure value. We'll trace one real ticket through this process during your shadowing week.

